§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬orthogonal complement❭ of a subset of an inner product
    space is the set of vectors which are orthogonal to every
    vector in the subset. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $(V, 𝗙)$ be a vector space and $U ⊂ V$. ⦉

  ‖ We denote the orthogonal complement of $U$ by $U^{\perp}$. ⦉
⦉

